Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.94,0:00:08.02,Default,Mizuno,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.34,0:01:53.21,Default,Tamie,0000,0000,0000,,Sanae Mizuno, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.43,0:01:56.97,Default,Tamie,0000,0000,0000,,She and Kouchi often talked \Nabout books together.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.97,0:01:58.89,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,She was so young...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.89,0:02:00.59,Default,Reiko,0000,0000,0000,,I worry about her brothers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.59,0:02:03.61,Default,Tamie,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she had brothers?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.61,0:02:05.14,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,One is named Takeru.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.57,0:02:06.98,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,He's in my class.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.98,0:02:10.30,Default,Tamie,0000,0000,0000,,Dear me, this is so awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.30,0:02:13.23,Default,Tamie,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't a girl in your class \Nrecently die in an accident, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.58,0:02:17.11,Default,Ryouhei,0000,0000,0000,,After a death, there always follows a funeral.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.87,0:02:22.16,Default,Ryouhei,0000,0000,0000,,How very tired I am of funerals...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.20,0:02:26.87,Default,Ryouhei,0000,0000,0000,,So very tired of funerals...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.27,0:02:30.65,Default,Board,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}June 4 (Thurs.)
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.40,0:02:32.44,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,The news about Mizuno's \Nsister comes as a terrible shock,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.12,0:02:34.25,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,but it will be all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.76,0:02:38.04,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,If we all try hard together, \Nwe can overcome this.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.20,0:03:03.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.66,0:03:05.88,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,She died.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.49,0:03:09.42,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Mizuno's sister died in \Nan accident yesterday.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.29,0:03:12.25,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Oh...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.76,0:03:20.76,Default,Board,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Self-Study - Sketching
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.96,0:03:30.39,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder what's wrong \Nwith Ms. Mikami.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.57,0:03:33.88,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe she's really sick.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.28,0:03:36.22,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,She didn't look too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.50,0:03:37.41,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,I hope she doesn't...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.84,0:03:39.77,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Sakakibara?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.22,0:03:41.07,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.07,0:03:44.80,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,You don't think Ms. Mikami \Nhas some serious,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.80,0:03:46.95,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,life-threatening illness, do you?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.95,0:03:50.23,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure she's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.23,0:03:51.56,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,You're probably right.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.86,0:03:54.25,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Are you that worried?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.66,0:03:59.02,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Well, after what happened \Nto Sakuragi...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.38,0:04:01.89,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,And now Mizuno's sister...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.89,0:04:03.02,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,So I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.02,0:04:04.22,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Are they related?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.22,0:04:06.16,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a connection \Nbetween these accidents?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.16,0:04:08.82,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.71,0:04:16.10,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you going?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.10,0:04:17.31,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,To do some research.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.61,0:04:25.11,Default,Book,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Yomiyama Prefectural Junior High School \NClass of 1972
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.82,0:04:35.08,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Who am I kidding?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.08,0:04:37.29,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Of course I wouldn't find Misaki's name here.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.61,0:04:47.85,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.17,0:04:50.60,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,You found your mother?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.99,0:04:51.84,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.72,0:04:55.88,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Interesting... So she graduated in '72.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.83,0:04:59.01,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Which class was she in?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.94,0:05:02.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Class 3, like me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.49,0:05:05.70,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Oh? Which one is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.25,0:05:08.12,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,This one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.36,0:05:11.12,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Ritsuko?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.10,0:05:13.45,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You knew her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.42,0:05:16.50,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.21,0:05:19.23,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,Ritsuko was...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:20.73,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.93,0:05:25.02,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I heard that she died. When was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.87,0:05:29.72,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,15 years ago, right after she had me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.72,0:05:31.34,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,15 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.43,0:05:35.00,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.74,0:05:37.44,Default,Chibiki,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.73,0:05:43.90,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Kouichi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.11,0:05:50.98,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Kubodera asked me to send \Nyou to the faculty room.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.76,0:05:53.49,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.13,0:05:59.75,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Let me apologize in advance.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.41,0:06:01.55,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.00,0:06:03.36,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,But this is for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.01,0:06:05.13,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,Forgive us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.00,0:06:11.85,Default,Police1,0000,0000,0000,,You are aware that Sanae Mizuno
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.85,0:06:15.43,Default,Police1,0000,0000,0000,,passed away in an accident at \Nthe hospital yesterday, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.67,0:06:16.40,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.40,0:06:20.31,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, am I suspected of something?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.48,0:06:23.01,Default,Police1,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, no. We know it was an accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.01,0:06:25.23,Default,Police1,0000,0000,0000,,A very unfortunate accident.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:25.57,0:06:28.32,Default,Police1,0000,0000,0000,,It's just, Ms. Mizuno's cell phone was
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.32,0:06:30.99,Default,Police1,0000,0000,0000,,found in the elevator in question.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.26,0:06:37.94,Default,Police1,0000,0000,0000,,Did you speak with her on the phone \Naround 1 p.m. yesterday?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.40,0:06:39.64,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.64,0:06:41.69,Default,Police1,0000,0000,0000,,She was on the roof at the time, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.98,0:06:45.83,Default,Police1,0000,0000,0000,,And she entered the \Nelevator from there...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.42,0:06:48.61,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What caused the accident?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.61,0:06:49.85,Default,Police2,0000,0000,0000,,That's under investigation.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.23,0:06:53.28,Default,Police2,0000,0000,0000,,All we know for certain is that the \Nsheaves holding the cables
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.28,0:06:55.47,Default,Police2,0000,0000,0000,,in place came loose, causing it to fall.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.54,0:06:59.29,Default,Police2,0000,0000,0000,,That building is several decades old,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.29,0:07:02.51,Default,Police2,0000,0000,0000,,and it's been through numerous \Nstructural modifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.51,0:07:04.27,Default,Mizuno,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Let's both be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.27,0:07:07.11,Default,Mizuno,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Especially where unusual \Naccidents are concerned.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.26,0:07:35.26,Default,Board,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Aya Ayano | Izumi Akazawa
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.95,0:07:35.26,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Sakakibara.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.65,0:07:39.63,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Are the police finished questioning you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.63,0:07:40.44,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.82,0:07:41.95,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.95,0:07:44.87,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're dismissed for the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.60,0:07:47.61,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Um, where is everyone?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.05,0:07:50.19,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,The new female class officer
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.19,0:07:52.33,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,was selected during homeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.33,0:07:54.04,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,It's Akazawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.04,0:07:56.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But, where'd everybody go?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.70,0:07:59.47,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Please be sure to uphold
Dialogue: 0,0:07:59.47,0:08:01.67,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,the class rules at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.14,0:08:03.52,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Are we clear?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.18,0:08:24.10,Default,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Who is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.79,0:08:26.02,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.10,0:08:28.87,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.40,0:08:30.48,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Walk home with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.78,0:08:38.76,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Where did everyone go \Nduring sixth period?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.48,0:08:41.92,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,To the meeting room, \Nto take care of some stuff.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.92,0:08:42.97,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.74,0:08:49.63,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,You've had a lot of strange experiences \Nsince you came here, haven't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.27,0:08:52.17,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,If you know, can you tell me \Nwhat's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.72,0:08:55.09,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, I can't.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.09,0:08:57.80,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Only, that something very unpleasant
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.80,0:09:00.10,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,might happen to you soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.47,0:09:01.47,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.27,0:09:03.98,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,At the meeting,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.46,0:09:07.63,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Akazawa said we needed \Nto discuss something,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.63,0:09:09.23,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,without you there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.62,0:09:13.41,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,But even if you don't \Nlike what happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.77,0:09:15.43,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,try to deal with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.88,0:09:17.99,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Remember that you're doing it for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.99,0:09:19.20,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Please.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.58,0:09:20.99,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,"All of us"?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.82,0:09:23.35,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}This is for all of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.83,0:09:24.66,Default,Izumi,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Forgive us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.46,0:09:28.29,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is this one of those class rules?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.83,0:09:29.64,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.57,0:09:33.22,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I just don't get it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.07,0:09:42.14,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Can I ask one favor?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.40,0:09:43.28,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.71,0:09:46.64,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I want a copy of the class roster.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.06,0:09:49.53,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,You didn't get one?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.17,0:09:52.97,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,It's just not fair.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.69,0:09:58.12,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,I can't agree with Akazawa's \Nway of handling things.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.67,0:10:01.26,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,It's not fair of her to force her own ideas
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.26,0:10:02.62,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,on the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.62,0:10:05.99,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,There must be so many \Nthings you want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.52,0:10:07.60,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,There are.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.06,0:10:10.31,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,Then you can ask me.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.86,0:10:12.86,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you everything I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.86,0:10:15.39,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Takabayashi, wait! Are you serious?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.94,0:10:16.83,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.43,0:10:18.93,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Does Mei Misaki exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.32,0:10:21.67,Default,Takabayashi,0000,0000,0000,,Mei Misaki is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.55,0:10:30.01,Default,Mochizuki,0000,0000,0000,,Takabayashi! Takabayashi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.63,0:10:59.36,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning. You're early today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.52,0:11:10.27,Default,Board,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}June 5 (Fri.)
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.97,0:11:23.69,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,That's it. Any other...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.29,0:11:26.20,Default,Kazami,0000,0000,0000,,No, forget it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.94,0:11:29.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did something happen this morning?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.09,0:11:38.19,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Let us pray that the soul of \Nour classmate, Takabayashi,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.78,0:11:40.58,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,may rest in peace.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.33,0:11:43.53,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Many sad events have transpired,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.02,0:11:46.21,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,but do not lose heart, \Nand do not give up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.21,0:11:48.93,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,We'll get through this together.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.30,0:11:52.98,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Remember to uphold the \Nclass rules at all times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.67,0:11:56.72,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Ms. Mikami is in a difficult position,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.72,0:11:59.64,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,but she has agreed to cooperate \Nto the best of her ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.64,0:12:02.45,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Does everyone understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.46,0:12:12.68,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.06,0:12:18.50,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What's with him?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.97,0:12:21.05,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, Wakui?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.75,0:12:26.13,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.36,0:12:43.55,Default,Phone,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}The customer you are trying \Nto reach currently
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.55,0:12:46.57,Default,Phone,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}has their phone off or is \Nout of the service area.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.54,0:12:50.42,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.04,0:12:53.91,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Listen...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.91,0:12:55.09,Default,Teshigawara,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.33,0:13:06.73,Default,Board,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Figures of Speech\NSimile, Metaphor, Personification
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.63,0:13:01.83,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,"A rumor walks alone."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.83,0:13:04.87,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Here, we see something \Nthat is not human
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.87,0:13:08.29,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,being expressed as \Ndisplaying human behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.29,0:13:11.26,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,This is known as personification.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.12,0:13:14.41,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,The important thing to \Nunderstand is that
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.41,0:13:20.60,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,human attributes are given \Nto something non-human.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.79,0:13:27.44,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Pascal once said, "Man is but a \Nreed, but he is a thinking reed."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.44,0:13:29.80,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,This is not personification.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.56,0:13:31.45,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what they meant.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.35,0:13:31.99,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,It is a metaphor.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.60,0:13:33.91,Default,Kubodera,0000,0000,0000,,Does that make sense?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.50,0:14:16.48,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Hi.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.56,0:14:19.54,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.90,0:14:21.63,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Your call was unexpected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.37,0:14:33.87,Default,Note,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Sorry. Ask Misaki to explain. -Mochizuki
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.62,0:14:38.37,Default,Note,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}{\s1}24 Mei Misaki
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.06,0:14:41.23,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,So, you got a copy of the class roster.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.23,0:14:42.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.66,0:14:44.10,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Let me start from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.74,0:14:47.15,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Did you hear that Takabayashi died?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:48.34,0:14:49.97,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,He had a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.52,0:14:52.34,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I know he had heart problems, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.86,0:14:53.80,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.37,0:14:57.12,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The second June death \Nwas caused by illness.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.42,0:14:59.98,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, when I got to school today,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.98,0:15:01.58,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,the whole class was acting weird.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.09,0:15:06.17,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Like they'd all conspired to \Ntreat me like I wasn't there.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.99,0:15:09.23,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,So that's what they decided to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.75,0:15:13.30,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Does this mean I'm just like you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.71,0:15:19.75,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,How does it feel to not exist?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.49,0:15:22.41,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Not so great.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.41,0:15:24.84,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But, in a way, it's a load off my mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.84,0:15:25.82,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It is?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.60,0:15:29.07,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Because now I know that you exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.51,0:15:37.28,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,This is where you live, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.28,0:15:38.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.45,0:15:40.54,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you figured \Nthat out long ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.01,0:15:43.29,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You did say you lived around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.29,0:15:44.99,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And you're not a customer.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.99,0:15:47.69,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Was that your mother who \Nanswered the phone?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.81,0:15:50.28,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She was surprised.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.28,0:15:54.39,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I very rarely get calls \Nfrom schoolmates.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.05,0:15:58.82,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is Kirika your mom?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.24,0:16:02.16,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I guess you'd call it a pseudonym.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.16,0:16:03.72,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,She goes by Kirika.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.51,0:16:07.17,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,A strange woman, \Nwho keeps herself cloistered
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.17,0:16:08.37,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,in the studio upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.68,0:16:11.99,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Does the "M" in "Studio M" \Nstand for Misaki?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.51,0:16:14.23,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It all makes sense now, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.51,0:16:19.87,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Let's go upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.99,0:16:34.36,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Did you know this was here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.69,0:16:43.56,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.16,0:16:54.83,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Why don't you ask the questions?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.83,0:16:56.57,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It might be easier to explain \Neverything that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.90,0:17:00.33,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I thought you hated being questioned.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.83,0:17:01.90,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.90,0:17:03.02,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But today,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.17,0:17:06.42,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'll make a special exception.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.96,0:17:10.30,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,First of all, Mei Misaki,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.30,0:17:11.80,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,you exist, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.27,0:17:15.13,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Did you think I was a ghost?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.13,0:17:16.22,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Sort of.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.79,0:17:18.98,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I guess you couldn't help it.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.57,0:17:21.56,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But your doubts are gone now, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.91,0:17:24.23,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Now that you know I exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.23,0:17:26.19,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,as a living human.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.82,0:17:31.05,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I'm only nonexistent to \Nthe others in class 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:32.03,0:17:33.17,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Since when?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.57,0:17:35.99,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It started on May 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.41,0:17:37.89,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,That's pretty recent.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.24,0:17:42.69,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Lots of things seemed strange \Nto you from the start, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.55,0:17:45.52,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And nobody would tell me why.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.22,0:17:49.87,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Not explaining the situation \Nto you beforehand
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.87,0:17:51.40,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,was a costly mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.40,0:17:52.61,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Mistake?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.49,0:17:56.59,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,You were supposed to treat me \Nas someone who didn't exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.59,0:17:59.74,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,just like everyone else in class.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.83,0:18:03.91,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But now you've ended up the same as me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.27,0:18:05.56,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,How awful for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.98,0:18:08.57,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,It's not exactly bullying...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.12,0:18:11.41,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think anybody thinks of it that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.65,0:18:19.60,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,I understand that I \Nno longer exist to them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.05,0:18:21.70,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But why are they doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.22,0:18:25.18,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's a natural question.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.83,0:18:29.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Remember the story about the \NMisaki who died 26 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.11,0:18:29.96,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.45,0:18:33.14,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That was the trigger.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.14,0:18:36.67,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,After that, class 3 drew closer to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.26,0:18:38.34,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Death?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.34,0:18:40.52,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It first happened to class 3
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.52,0:18:45.10,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,the year after Misaki's \Nclassmates graduated.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.70,0:18:49.71,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,And once it happens, once it begins,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.71,0:18:51.80,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,somebody dies each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.69,0:18:56.07,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Either a student, or \Nsomeone from their family.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.34,0:18:57.59,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,What is "it"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.22,0:19:00.28,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's when...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.21,0:19:04.99,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,...the number of students in \Nthe class increases by one.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.57,0:19:07.58,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Increases? Who?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.14,0:19:10.58,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody knows.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.22,0:19:16.18,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They can never figure out \Nwho the extra one is.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.57,0:19:17.59,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Extra one?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.51,0:19:22.30,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,25 years ago, shortly \Nafter the new term began,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.30,0:19:23.86,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,they realized that the classroom
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.86,0:19:25.73,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,was short one desk and chair,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.49,0:19:28.22,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,even though they had prepared enough
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.22,0:19:30.00,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,for all of the students.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.90,0:19:33.90,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Couldn't they just check \Nthe school records?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.16,0:19:36.37,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They did, but there was no point.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.79,0:19:40.33,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The roster and records had been \Naltered to be inconsistent.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.72,0:19:43.45,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They were just one \Ndesk and chair short.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.09,0:19:46.00,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So, someone rewrote the numbers?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.43,0:19:47.80,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I used the word "altered" figuratively.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.28,0:19:52.26,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They say that everyone's \Nmemories had changed as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.26,0:19:53.18,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.02,0:19:56.02,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Sounds impossible, doesn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.86,0:20:00.51,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But it's supposedly true.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.27,0:20:05.82,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I was told this type of \Nphenomenon could happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.58,0:20:07.54,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Phenomenon?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.05,0:20:11.11,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,At first, everyone thought \Nit was just an error
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.11,0:20:12.45,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and thought nothing of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.84,0:20:17.08,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But starting in April, \Npeople connected to the class
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.08,0:20:18.87,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,started to die each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.87,0:20:19.91,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Each month?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.47,0:20:22.00,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,For the whole year?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.00,0:20:25.02,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That year, I think it was six students
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.02,0:20:27.01,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and ten family members.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.54,0:20:29.28,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Clearly abnormal, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.28,0:20:33.71,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,This phenomenon has continued \Nin class 3 ever since.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.14,0:20:36.95,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So, a 9th grade class 3 student
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.95,0:20:39.14,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,named Misaki died 26 years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.61,0:20:40.99,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,And starting the next year,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.99,0:20:43.80,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,there was somehow an extra \Nstudent in the class.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.29,0:20:48.27,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Then, people connected to the \Nclass started to die each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.31,0:20:52.64,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,But why do people die when \Nthere's an extra student?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.77,0:20:55.32,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Nobody knows the reason.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.32,0:20:57.04,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That's just what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.04,0:21:00.39,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Plus, that extra student is...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.89,0:21:03.22,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,...someone dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.14,0:21:08.31,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,You mean the Misaki who \Ndied 26 years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.87,0:21:14.87,Default,Desk,0000,0000,0000,,{\a6}Who is dead?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.53,0:21:14.20,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Is it a ghost or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.87,0:21:18.47,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's different from \Nwhat we'd call a ghost.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.47,0:21:20.16,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It seems to have a physical body.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.63,0:21:23.75,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way to tell it apart \Nfrom the rest of us.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.21,0:21:25.38,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,No way to tell?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.95,0:21:30.14,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The dead person has \Na soul and memories,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.14,0:21:33.59,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and they don't realize they're dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.45,0:21:36.20,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Who are they?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.63,0:21:39.17,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,The people connected to the class \Nwho have died over the years.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.08,0:21:45.78,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,This is how I see it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.08,0:21:48.22,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Class 3's actions 26 years ago
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.22,0:21:51.48,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,made the class a place \Nthat invites the dead in.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.88,0:21:55.09,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,After that, the dead \Nbegan to join the class,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.09,0:21:58.18,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and class 3 drew closer to death.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.22,0:22:01.31,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,In response,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.96,0:22:05.74,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,the class 3 students \Ncame up with several
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.74,0:22:08.30,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,countermeasures to try \Nto escape this calamity.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.05,0:22:10.58,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Like exorcisms?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.05,0:22:12.29,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Possibly.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.14,0:22:15.20,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,They tried moving to a \Ndifferent classroom,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.20,0:22:18.22,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and changing the name of \Nclass 3 to class C.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.67,0:22:20.88,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,But that didn't stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.34,0:22:22.90,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,So the problem is with the students
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.90,0:22:24.34,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,in the 9th grade's third class?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.72,0:22:25.94,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Seems to be.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:26.63,0:22:29.75,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Then, about ten years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.27,0:22:32.63,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,they found a way to \Ndeal with the problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.35,0:22:38.46,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,A method that prevented \Npeople from dying each month.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.50,0:22:41.42,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.02,0:22:43.90,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,Treat one student like they don't exist,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.90,0:22:46.42,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,to make up for the extra person.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.98,0:22:50.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,That way, they return the \Nclass to its correct number,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.17,0:22:54.43,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,and they can avoid the \Ncalamity for that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.67,0:22:57.04,Default,Mei,0000,0000,0000,,It's a sort of charm.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.93,0:24:40.26,Default,Kouichi,0000,0000,0000,,Face to face.
